gomodel:SYNGO_423  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig. 1: Cntnap4 is present at presynaptic fraction, Fc-tagged Cntnap4 binds to soma and proximal dendrites, apposed to gephyrin puncta.\n\n13/4/2017 Pim\n- Cntnap4 has a TM domain. The Fc-tagged Cntnap4 construct is the extracellular domain of this protein. Fig.1 suggests that Cntnap4 is a presynaptic TM protein that interacts with proteins attached to gephyrin-positive postsynaptic elements. For this to occur the protein must be positioned in the presynaptic plasma membrane. This is not directly shown, but implied in the paper.\n- \"Integral component ...\" is inferred form the TM domain of Cntnap4.. Experimental description: Biochemical fractionation was performed using mouse brain, the in vitro staining with Fc-tagged Cntnap4 extracellular domain was done on rat neurons, cDNA species for Fc-tagged Cntnap4 extracellular domain was not specified. These experiments are featured in Fig. 1.\n\nLitteral from M&M\n\"Presynaptic and postsynaptic fractionation. Synaptosomal fractions from mouse\nbrain were prepared as described previously\"\n\"Hippocampal cultures. Cultures were prepared from embryonic day 19 Sprague\nDawley ratembryonic brain tissue.\"\n\n13/4/2017 Pim:\n- data in Fig.1D on rat material is sufficient to claim the selected term \"presynapse\". Therefore mouse is the correctly annotated protein. The recombinant Cntnap4-Fc protein is used to justify the AE to GABAergic synapse." , "Automated change 2024-03-14: GO:0099056 replaced by GO:0042734" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-2949-9725" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0003-0662-9523" ;
        dc:date           "2024-03-14" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_423" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10090" .

